description: This trip is best done using a mountain bike to access Kakwa Lake. It is a 30 km. bike ride along the McGregor River using an old Quarry access road. There is a BC Parks cabin to use on a first come basis. Alternately, there is a tent camp site there as well.
directions: West of McBride,BC or east of Prince George,BC., drive to the Walker Creek FSR. Drive this road for 73 kms. to its terminus at Bastille Creek.
title: Kakwa Lake
